# Copy this file to `.env.imprint` at the repository root (same directory as this example).
# `.env.imprint` is gitignored — use it for your legal imprint (Impressum) text only on machines
# and in CI that deploy production builds.
#
# The PWA (`frontend/`) and marketing site (`landing-page/`) read this file at build time via
# `load-imprint-env.mjs` and inject `VITE_IMPRINT` into the client bundle.
#
# Production: ensure `.env.imprint` exists before `npm run build` (or set the same value in your
# CI secrets and write it to that file in the build step).

# Plain text. Use \n for line breaks in a single line, or use double-quoted multiline (dotenv).
# VITE_IMPRINT=Angaben gemäß § 5 TMG:\n\nMax Mustermann\nMusterstraße 1\n12345 Musterstadt\n\nKontakt: mail@example.com

VITE_IMPRINT="Impressum (example — replace in your local .env.imprint)\n\nProvider: …\nAddress: …\nContact: …"
